Under the optimized conditions discussed above, the linear response of CDs-AAP to OCl– acid was detected in Tris-HCl buffer (pH 7.0). As depicted in Fig. 9
                        A, with increasing the concentration of OCl–, the fluorescence intensity of CDs-AAP exhibits a decrease tendency. When the concentration of OCl– reaches 36 μM, the fluorescence of CDs-AAP can be efficiently quenched to approximately 70.4% of its initial value. The relationship between the fluorescence intensity (F0–F) and OCl– concentration is linear in the 3 − 36 μM range of OCl– concentration (the inset in Fig. 9A). The fluorescence intensity is given by F0–F = 21.27676[OCl–] + 58.56169 (R2 = 0.9925). On the basis of 3σ/k, where σ is the standard deviation of blank signal of CDs-AAP and k is the slope of the calibration curve, the detection limit for OCl– was estimated to be 40 nM, which is lower than some other fluorescent probes for OCl– detection (Table 1
                        ). Moreover, the relationship between the fluorescence intensity of the small polar CDs-AAP and the OCl– concentration was also analyzed, and the detection limit was 56 nM, which confirmed a smaller amount of AAP was grafted (Fig. S6).
